    <section id="lunisolar">
      <h2>Lunisolar Mechanics</h2>

      <div class="comparison-grid">
        <div class="comparison-card comparison-card--positive">
          <h3>Lunar Component</h3>
          <p>Months follow new moons: 29 or 30 days each (avg. 29.53). Twelve lunar months total ~354 days — 11 short of the solar year. <strong>Intercalary months</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">閏月</span>) inserted ~7 times every 19 years (Metonic cycle).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="comparison-card comparison-card--positive">
          <h3>Solar Component</h3>
          <p>The <strong>24 Solar Terms</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">節氣</span>) divide the sun's annual path into 24 segments of ~15 days. They determine which month receives an intercalary insertion and anchor the calendar to agricultural seasons.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="solar-terms">
      <h2>The 24 Solar Terms (<span class="chinese-char">二十四節氣</span>)</h2>

      <div class="image-panel">
